  "prompt": "What are some good colleges in India that I can still apply to their MBA program for this year\u2019s session?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, some of the top MBA colleges in India that you may still be able to apply to for the 2023-2025 academic session (or similar timelines) include:\n\n### **Top Tier MBA Colleges (with late or rolling admissions)**\n1. **Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs)**  \n   - Some newer IIMs (e.g., IIM Bodh Gaya, IIM Jammu, IIM Sirmaur) may still have CAP (Common Admission Process) rounds open.  \n   - Check their official websites for updates.\n\n2. **ISB (Indian School of Business)**  \n   - ISB Hyderabad and Mohali may have admissions open for their one-year PGP program.  \n   - Deadlines vary, so check their website for details.\n\n3. **XLRI Xavier School of Management**  \n   - XLRI Jamshedpur may still accept applications for its PGDM programs.  \n   - Keep an eye on their website for any open rounds.\n\n4. **SP Jain Institute of Management and Research (SPJIMR)**  \n   - SPJIMR Mumbai may have rolling admissions for its PGDM program.  \n   - Check their website for details.\n\n5. **Symbiosis Institute of Business Management (SIBM Pune)**  \n   - SNAP (Symbiosis National Aptitude Test) registrations may still be open for MBA admissions.  \n   - Visit the official SNAP website for details.\n\n6. **NMIMS School of Business Management**  \n   - NMIMS Mumbai may still have open rounds for its MBA program.  \n   - Check their official website for updates.\n\n7. **IIFT (Indian Institute of Foreign Trade)**  \n   - IIFT Delhi and Kolkata may have admissions open for their MBA (International Business) program.  \n   - Visit their website for deadlines.\n\n8. **MDI Gurgaon**  \n   - Management Development Institute (MDI) Gurgaon may still accept applications for its PGPM and PGP-HRM programs.  \n   - Check their official website for updates.\n\n### **Other Good MBA Colleges (with Open Admissions)**\n1. **IMT Ghaziabad**  \n   - IMT Ghaziabad may still have open rounds for its PGDM program.  \n   - Visit their website for details.\n\n2. **Great Lakes Institute of Management, Chennai**  \n   - Great Lakes may still accept applications for its PGPM and PGDM programs.  \n   - Check their website for updates.\n\n3. **TAPMI Manipal (T.A. Pai Management Institute)**  \n   - TAPMI may still have open admissions for its PGDM program.  \n   - Visit their website for details.\n\n4. **KJ Somaiya Institute of Management, Mumbai**  \n   - KJ Somaiya may still accept applications for its MBA program.  \n   - Check their official website.\n\n5. **Goa Institute of Management (GIM)**  \n   - GIM may still have open rounds for its PGDM program.  \n   - Visit their website for updates.\n\n### **Steps to Take:**\n1. **Visit Official Websites**: Check the official websites of the colleges for the latest admission notifications and deadlines.\n2. **Entrance Exam Scores**: Most top colleges accept CAT, XAT, GMAT, or other exam scores. Ensure you have a valid score.\n3. **Direct Applications**: Some colleges may accept direct applications without entrance exam scores (e.g., based on academic performance or work experience).\n4. **Contact Admissions Offices**: Reach out to the admissions offices of the colleges you\u2019re interested in for clarification on deadlines and application processes.\n\n### **Pro Tip**: Act quickly, as deadlines for many programs are approaching or may have already passed. Good luck with your MBA applications!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
